==English==

===Etymology===
Afrikaans: ''berg'': mountain

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}
#(South African regional English)  A homeless person in the Cape Town. So called because they used to live in the mountains.
#*"The man then joined a group of''' bergies''' sleeping near the police station and pretended to be one of them when confronted by the rangers. But he was betrayed by a long trail of [[perlemoen]] slime leading from the road to the '''bergies'''' sleeping spot."

